      "passage": [
        {
          "text": "Mia and Ben went to the lake by bus because their father was working. They planned to swim, but the water was too cold, so they hired two small boats for an hour instead. After lunch they walked along the nature path and visited the bird house before taking the bus home. Mia brought sandwiches and a camera, while Ben carried a map of the walking routes. They stopped at the visitor centre to learn about ducks and took photographs from a wooden bridge. Before leaving, they bought postcards for their parents and checked the bus timetable carefully. The weather changed in the afternoon, so they put on their jackets and stayed close to the shore. Ben wanted to fish, but fishing was not allowed there. They agreed to return in summer when the water would be warmer."
        }
